content.description:
Inside corner on the left side of this buttress, to a deep corner behind the projecting block.  Finish directly up the overhang on huge jugs.  (Route 12 in Swartling & Mayer.)

 No gear initially, but great once you get to the deep corner.
content.protection: Standard rack.  A big piece for the top of the deep crack below the overhang.
content.location: The buttress left of the Frigate.  Scramble up to the ledge system, and continue straight up.

content.description:
Fun lead that shares the start to Oh Rats. When you get to the top of the large ledge (referred to as the "second ledge in Swartling), head South West (climbers left) up short 4th class scramble to thin crack to top out. Walk off climbers left.

 This is route number 3 in this area, in the Swartling Guide.
content.protection: After the initial moves, the start eats cams... master cam #1 up to C4 #2.  Nuts also work well...

content.description:
Starting from the ledge/ramp, move up just left of the right corner of this buttress, into the right-facing corner system.  Follow this to the top.  (Route 13 in Swartling & Mayer.)

 You could also start from near the base of the Pooper, and add 15 feet below the major ledge.
content.location: Just left of the Frigate, scramble up onto the ledge system that crosses the buttress.

content.description: Climb overhanging dihedral with crack, to overhang traverse right and around corner to short face(crux)   Var, 5.11d , pull overhang directly,

Climb up slabby corner directly to the climbers right of the start of Thin Fingers/Ohh Rats.  Jug city as you walk your way up slab to tight squeeze finish.  Walk off climbers right... 

  This is route number 5 in this area, in the Swartling Guide.
content.protection: Protects well and is a very easy climb, but due to the slabby awkward nature of route as well as rocks jutting out from walls, there is not much margin of error if you peel off.  You will get ground up...

content.description:
In memory of Art Grahn, who loved playing on quartzite.

 Start in the middle of the buttress, heading up into the broken blocks in the middle of the face.  Continue straight up, the crux.  (Not documented in Swartling & Mayer.)
content.protection: Neither the initial moves nor the crux at the top has any gear - TR this one.
content.location: Scramble up onto the ledge system, left of the Frigate.

pathTokens: West Bluff 02 - Misery Rocks & The Pantry

content.description: Dutchman Rampart is a group of broken walls and buttresses, north of Misery and west of The Frigate. The area contains a dozen moderate climbs, mostly short.
